x, place pan juices from roast plus stock to make 1 litre, 50 g plain flour, salt and pepper to taste in mixing bowl then cook 12-15 minutes\/Varoma\/speed 2.","Few things say roast dinner more than lamb. This dish uses surprisingly few ingredients for such a flavoursome result. This is a great dish for get-togethers – it’s beautifully tender and looks really impressive in the middle of the table, ready for carving. Best enjoyed in the spring when British lamb is available."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","2h 30m","8 portions"]}